# Mobile App (Expo / React Native)

## REQUIRED skills (read & follow before building any mobile UI)
When designing, building, refactoring, or reviewing ANY code in `apps/mobile/**`, you MUST
read and follow these skills first:
- `building-native-ui` — Expo Router structure, native controls, headers/tabs, styling, animations.
- `vercel-react-native-skills` — RN/Expo performance: list virtualization, memoization, GPU-only
  animations, expo-image, native navigation.

Treat them as mandatory pre-work, not optional references.

## Conventions
- Expo SDK 51 + `expo-router`. Functional components, no default-export components.
- Use `expo-image` (with `sf:` SF Symbols where appropriate), NOT `img` or `@expo/vector-icons`.
- Capture flow uses `expo-image-picker`; POST multipart to Go `/score/photo`.
- Render the SAME result component shape as web via shared types in `packages/shared-types`.
- `ScrollView`/`FlatList` with `contentInsetAdjustmentBehavior="automatic"`; respect safe areas.
- Animate only `transform` / `opacity`. Memoize list items. Use FlashList for large lists.
- Never use removed RN modules (Picker, WebView, SafeAreaView, AsyncStorage); use `process.env.EXPO_OS` not `Platform.OS`.
